[SN]TITLE[SN]
Christian Bagley death: Dog walker may have 'key information'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Police have said someone walking a dog near to where a father-of-one was stabbed in Hereford may hold "key information" for their murder investigations.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Christian Bagley, 30, from the city, was found with stab wounds on 21 June after visiting his daughter.
Police said the person was seen walking a German Shepherd sized dark coloured dog near Hunderton Bridge at night.
Three men were arrested on suspicion of murder and released without charge.
Det Ch Insp Leighton Harding said: "We would like to trace this individual as they may hold key information which could assist our investigation."
Mr Bagley was stabbed near the bridge in Hereford between 22:40 and 23:00 BST, West Mercia Police said.
